[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 15:2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 15:2",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Every creditor that lendeth aught shall release it ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— This cannot be meant of money lent to those who had borrowed it for the purchase of lands, trade, or other improvements, and who were able to pay; for nothing could have been more absurd than to have extinguished such debts, whereby the borrower was enriched. But it must be understood of money lent to an Israelite who was in poor circumstances, as appears from verse",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4. According to this law, every poor Israelite who had borrowed money, and had not been able to pay it before, should this year be released from it. And though, if he were able, he was bound in conscience to pay it afterward, yet it could not be recovered by law. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "His brother ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— This is added to limit the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "neighbour, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "which is more general, unto a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "brother, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in nation and religion, an Israelite. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Lord’s release — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a release for the Lord, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in obedience to his command, for his honour, and as an acknowledgment of his right in your estates, and of his kindness in giving and continuing them to you.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
